Description: Shoulder fragment of a pottery belly amphora or oinochoe; streaky black glaze on the inside of the neck; outside covered in shiny glaze fired bright red; narrow red stripe at tranistion from neck to body. Hard, light brown clay, Munsell 2.5YR 6/4 (light reddish brown); fine dark mica.
Bibliographic references: Weber 2012 / Untersuchungen zur archaischen griechischen Keramik aus anderen ägyptischen Fundorten (TD 341)
Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.129)
Acquisition notes: Found unregistered in the Department in 2010, in a box with other sherds from Tell Dafana.
